      "content": "it's not just a leap though. i noticed the timing of the updates matches up weirdly with these crowd-sourced biometric data streams from wearable tech. it's like they are using the OS to sync the biological side with the digital side. do you think it's possible they are using the kernel level access to bypass all standard privacy encryption so they can access the unfiltered human response data?",
